<TITLE> Brahmanbaria police recover 10 year-old's body in pieces </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, July 18 (bdnews24.com)  Police, in a horrific discovery, recovered the body of 10 year-old in six pieces, in Brahmanbaria on Saturday. The young boy was identified as Sami, son of Shafiqul Islam, and a student of Bagaura Government Primary School in Nabinagar Upazila. "The child was killed in a horrific incident," Morshed Alam, an assistant sub-inspector of of Nabinagar Police Station, said. He said police were doing all to find out who was behind the killing. "No one has been arrested yet," Alam said. A case was being filed with Nabinagar Police Station. bdn
